snippet.textDisplay: We watched this live and got really annoyed by the camera changing angles the whole time, it would have been a lot better if you just stayed on the courtyard view of the castle with the fireworks above, there was no need to change angles every 5 sec to way close up on the castle then way zoomed out looking at the roads and cars next to the park with the fireworks, it really ruined the show for us since it changed so quickly and when there was a show on the castle that we just took an interest in, you zoomed out to the parking lot again so the castle wasn't even visible. I hope in the future you will pick a good angle and leave it there instead.

snippet.textDisplay: I watch coverage from all over the world, as the various countries and time zones welcome in the New Year. Each year, I find myself comparing all of them to Disney fireworks.  Sorry, I guess nothing comes close to a display like this.  I think being at Disney and watching it in person, spoiled me,lol.
